<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Unit tests fail on some platforms (mine is Ubuntu 10.10 running PHP 5.3.3) because OPENSSL_ALGO_MD2 is no longer defined.  This is because the OpenSSL library has discontinued MD2 because it is insecure.  Should all support of MD2 be removed from Zend_Crypt as well?  It will be non functional on these platforms anyway.</p>

<p>The specific unit test failure:</p>

<pre class="literal">
Zend_Crypt_RsaTest::testConstructorSetsHashOption
Use of undefined constant OPENSSL_ALGO_MD2 - assumed 'OPENSSL_ALGO_MD2'

/library/Zend/Crypt/Rsa.php:267
library/Zend/Crypt/Rsa.php:106
/library/Zend/Crypt/Rsa.php:82
/tests/Zend/Crypt/Rsa/RsaTest.php:138
